## Key Design Decisions & Rationale

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| CTC loss over cross-entropy | Handles variable-length sequences without forced alignment |
| Curriculum learning (short clips first) | Stabilises early CTC training; avoids blank collapse |
| Grayscale input | Lip shape is carried in structure, not colour; reduces memory |
| MC3D frontend over custom 3D CNN | Matches published LRS2 architecture standard; proven capacity |
| Per-frame ResNet18 over full 3D ResNet | Memory efficient on T4; provides comparable representational power |
| 50 landmarks (40 lip + 10 chin) | Chin landmarks capture jaw drop — a key articulation signal often missed |
| No augmentation on landmark stream | Landmarks are too semantically dense; perturbations destroy signal |